definitions.definition: A river in New York and Pennsylvania , United States ; flowing from the confluence of the Tioga and Cohocton rivers at Painted Post , New York into the Susquehanna at Sayre , Pennsylvania.
A town in Chemung County , New York ; named for the river.
A census-designated place and township in McHenry County , Illinois .
An unincorporated community in McNett Township, Lycoming County , Pennsylvania .
